Document: AnimatedSprite2D  
Path: godot/classes/class_animatedsprite2d.rst  
Summary: Methods for controlling animation playback, state, and frame management in AnimatedSprite2D.  

Method: get_playing_speed() → float. Const method. Returns the current playback speed of the animation.  
Method: is_playing() → bool. Const method. Checks if the animation is currently playing.  
Method: pause(). Pauses the animation playback.  
Method: play(name: StringName = "", custom_speed: float = 1.0, from_end: bool = false). Starts playing the specified animation. If name is empty, uses the current animation. custom_speed adjusts the playback speed. from_end starts from the end of the animation if true.  
Method: play_backwards(name: StringName = ""). Plays the specified animation in reverse. If name is empty, uses the current animation.  
Method: set_frame_and_progress(frame: int, progress: float). Sets the current frame and progress within the animation.  
Method: stop(). Stops the animation and resets it to the beginning.
