Document: AnimatedSprite2D  
Path: godot/classes/class_animatedsprite2d.rst  
Summary: Properties and member variables of the AnimatedSprite2D class, including animation control, texture manipulation, and frame management.  

animation (StringName): The current animation from the sprite_frames resource. Default: "default". Changing this resets frame and frame_progress. Set/Get: set_animation(value), get_animation().  

autoplay (String): The animation key to play when the scene loads. Default: empty string. Set/Get: set_autoplay(value), get_autoplay().  

centered (bool): If true, texture is centered. Default: true. Note: For pixel art, set to false or enable snap_2d_vertices_to_pixel and snap_2d_transforms_to_pixel in ProjectSettings to avoid deformation. Set/Get: set_centered(value), is_centered().  

flip_h (bool): If true, texture is flipped horizontally. Default: false. Set/Get: set_flip_h(value), is_flipped_h().  

flip_v (bool): If true, texture is flipped vertically. Default: false. Set/Get: set_flip_v(value), is_flipped_v().  

frame (int): The displayed animation frame index. Default: 0. Setting this resets frame_progress. Use set_frame_and_progress() to avoid resetting progress. Set/Get: set_frame(value), get_frame().  

frame_progress (float): Progress between 0.0 and 1.0 for frame transitions. When playing backwards, transitions from 1.0 to 0.0. Default: 0.0. Set/Get: set_frame_progress(value), get_frame_progress().  

offset (Vector2): Texture drawing offset. Default: Vector2(0, 0). Set/Get: set_offset(value), get_offset().  

speed_scale (float): Animation speed scaling ratio. Default: 1.0. Negative values play animation in reverse. Zero stops animation. Set/Get: set_speed_scale(value), get_speed_scale().  

sprite_frames (SpriteFrames): The SpriteFrames resource containing animations. Allows loading, editing, and saving states. Set/Get: set_sprite_frames(value), get_sprite_frames().
---CHUNK---
Document: AnimatedSprite2D  
Path: godot/classes/class_animatedsprite2d.rst  
Summary: Methods for controlling animation playback, speed, and state in AnimatedSprite2D.  

get_playing_speed() → float  
Returns the actual playing speed of the current animation or 0 if not playing. This speed is calculated as the speed_scale property multiplied by the custom_speed argument from the play() method. Returns a negative value if the animation is playing backwards.  

is_playing() → bool  
Returns true if an animation is currently playing, even if speed_scale or custom_speed are 0.  

pause()  
Pauses the currently playing animation. The frame and frame_progress values are retained. Calling play() or play_backwards() without arguments resumes playback from the current position. See also stop().  

play(name: StringName = "", custom_speed: float = 1.0, from_end: bool = false)  
Plays the animation with the specified name. If custom_speed is negative and from_end is true, the animation plays backwards (equivalent to play_backwards()). If the same animation name is used or no name is provided, a paused animation resumes.  

play_backwards(name: StringName = "")  
Plays the animation in reverse. This is a shorthand for play() with custom_speed = -1.0 and from_end = true.  

set_frame_and_progress(frame: int, progress: float)  
Sets the frame and frame_progress properties to the specified values without resetting frame_progress to 0.0. Example:  
GDScript:  
    var current_frame = animated_sprite.get_frame()  
    var current_progress = animated_sprite.get_frame_progress()  
    animated_sprite.play("walk_another_skin")  
    animated_sprite.set_frame_and_progress(current_frame, current_progress)  

stop()  
Stops the currently playing animation, resetting the position to 0 and custom_speed to 1.0. See also pause().